Okay, let's build this landing page using React, Vite, and Tailwind CSS.

First, ensure you have Node.js and npm/yarn installed. Then, create a new Vite project:

```bash
npm create vite@latest gemini-dev-chatbot-landing --template react
# or
yarn create vite gemini-dev-chatbot-landing --template react

cd gemini-dev-chatbot-landing
npm install
# or
yarn install
```

Next, install Tailwind CSS:

```bash
npm install -D tailwindcss postcss autoprefixer
# or
yarn add -D tailwindcss postcss autoprefixer
```

Initialize Tailwind CSS:

```bash
npx tailwindcss init -p
```

This will create `tailwind.config.js` and `postcss.config.js`.

Configure `tailwind.config.js`:

```javascript
/** @type {import('tailwindcss').Config} */
export default {
  content: [
    "./index.html",
    "./src/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx}",
  ],
  theme: {
    extend: {
      colors: {
        'primary-dark': '#1A202C', // Dark Slate Gray
        'accent-blue': '#4299E1', // Royal Blue
        'subtle-blue': '#90CDF4', // Light Sky Blue
        'text-primary': '#E2E8F0', // Light Gray
        'text-secondary': '#A0AEC0', // Cool Gray
      },
      fontFamily: {
        // Using Inter and Roboto as specified
        heading: ['Inter', 'sans-serif'],
        body: ['Roboto', 'sans-serif'],
      },
    },
  },
  plugins: [],
}
```

Update your `src/index.css` (or create it if it doesn't exist) with Tailwind directives:

```css
@tailwind base;
@tailwind components;
@tailwind utilities;

/* Add custom base styles for dark mode and typography */
